  "notes": "Tongan (lea faka-Tonga), Polynesian, Kingdom of Tonga. Fully phonemic 17-letter orthography: 5 vowels with a phonemic length contrast written with the macron (toloi: ā ē ī ō ū), 12 consonants including the digraph ⟨ng⟩ /ŋ/ and the fakauʻa ⟨ʻ⟩ (U+02BB MODIFIER LETTER TURNED COMMA), a full consonant phoneme /ʔ/ that must stand between or before vowels. ⟨p⟩ /p/ and ⟨t⟩ /t/ are unaspirated. Syllables are open (CV/V). Input contract: the glottal stop must be written with U+02BB ⟨ʻ⟩; an ASCII apostrophe (') or a right single quote (’) is not recognised as a grapheme.",
